{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, information-theoretic entropy, introduced by Shannon, is a measure of uncertainty.",
    "Entropy in quantum physics refers to the information entropy rather than thermodynamic entropy.",
    "This confusion is common in many other sciences, but clearly, entropy as energy and entropy as information are not the same [23].",
    "Energy follows the laws of thermodynamics, whereas interchanges of information do not..",
    "The concept of entropy, even as a descriptor of phenomena of information in the same eld, i.e., ecology, has several meanings [24].Information senescence: Rather than using the term entropy in Infodynamics, we might refer to Information Senescence."
  ]
}